					  SCAGA Changes 2011 Spring Classic to One Round  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  May 12, 2011    No Comments  

					 

 The Stark County Amateur Golf Association announced today that the 2011 Spring Classic — originally scheduled as a 36-hole two-day individual stroke play event — will now be played as a single round 18-hole tournament.   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  Rain Washes out SCAGA 2-M Scramble  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  April 16, 2011    No Comments  

					 

 The lead group played 14 holes and the entire field of 64 made it through four, but eventually the intermittent rain turned into a steady downpour and the first event of the 2011 SCAGA season was a wash-out. 
 The next event on the SCAGA schedule is the 2-day, 36-hole Spring Classic,  May 21 at Tam O’Shanter Golf Course  in Canton and  May 22 at The Sanctuary Golf Club  in North Canton. To enter, visit  SCAGA.com . 

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  SCAGA Making Changes for 2011  

					 by Jeffrey Barbas  |  March 3, 2011    No Comments  

					 

 The Stark County Amateur Golf Association has made several user-friendly changes over the last few years. The biggest change has been the elimination of any membership fee to play in our events: each player pays the tournament entry fee, an optional skins game fee, and the golf course greens/cart fee (most of which have been discounted for our players) — and that’s it! 
 And there are some additional changes being made to SCAGA in 2011 that will benefit our players further.    [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  FINAL RESULTS: 2010 SCAGA Chippewa Medal Play  

					 by Jeffrey Barbas  |  August 15, 2010    No Comments  

					 

 Justin Lower and Richie Schembechler put on a show at Chippewa Golf Club in Doylestown on Sunday in the final 2o1o event of the Stark County Amateur Golf Association series. Both players finished with a sizzling-hot score of 5-under par 66.    [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

					  FINAL RESULTS: 2010 Stark County Amateur  

					 by Jeffrey Barbas  |  July 25, 2010    No Comments  

					 

 As the last group of the day was still grinding it out on the golf course in search of a win, Lucas Murray of East Sparta was sitting in the clubhouse waiting. 
 Starting the day tied for ninth place and five shots off the lead, Murray’s final round six-under par 65 at the Sanctuary Golf Club in North Canton was an incredible turn-around, giving him a three shot victory in the 2010 Stark County Amateur Golf Championship with a 54-hole total of even par 215.   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

