					  SCAGA 2010 Zoar 2-Man Scramble Results  

					 by Jeffrey Barbas  |  April 25, 2010    No Comments  

					 

   104 golfers converged on the 6,730 yard Zoar Village Golf Club for the annual opening Stark County Amateur Golf Association 2-man scramble tournament. The greens were in great shape as usual, fast and tricky for some of us. 
 The teams of Darren Phipps and Tom McBride tied with Richie Schembechler and Justin Lower at 12 under par to win the AA flight. Complete results follow.  [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

